### Hadith 1:547

*Narrated Jarir bin 'Abdullah:*

We were with the Prophet on a full moon night. He looked at the moon and
said, "You will certainly see your Lord as you see this moon, and there
will be no trouble in seeing Him. So if you can avoid missing (through
sleep, business, etc.) a prayer before the rising of the sun (Fajr) and
before its setting ('Asr) you must do so. He (the Prophet ) then recited
the following verse:

And celebrate the praises Of Your Lord before The rising of the sun And
before (its) setting." (50.39)

